\subsubsection{User}
\label{sec:controller_user}

\paragraph{}
The User controller is responsible for managing user registration, login and logout and account details. Its public actions are:

\begin{scriptsize}
\begin{verbatim}
user/login
user/logout
user/register
user/user_confirm
user/admin_confirm
user/reset_password
user/lost_password
user/account
user/account/update
user/lost_password
user/reset_password
user/set_experiment
\end{verbatim}
\end{scriptsize}

\paragraph{}
Registration has configuration settings in the rome.yml configuration file which determine whether or not confirmation (via email) is required for both the user and the administrator:

\begin{scriptsize}
\begin{verbatim}
registration:
    user_confirm: '1'
    admin_confirm: '1'
\end{verbatim}
\end{scriptsize}